Usage: ecoCompareNetlist [-help] [-logical] -outfile <fileName>
                         [-outputPhysicalInstInFile <physicalInstFile>] {-def <referenceFileName> [-referenceData <inMemory|external>]}

-help                                  # Prints out the command usage
-def <referenceFileName>               # Specifies the name of the DEF file
                                       # that EDI system uses to compare with
                                       # the design (string, required)
-logical                               # Compares the netlists for logical
                                       # equivalence (bool, optional)
-outfile <fileName>                    # Specifies the file name that contains
                                       # the differences between the specified
                                       # DEF file and the design in the
                                       # database (string, required)
-outputPhysicalInstInFile <physicalInstFile>
                                       # When this option is specified,
                                       # physical instance eco command is also
                                       # written to eco file, and dump added
                                       # physical instances name one per line
                                       # to <physicalInstFile> (string, optional)
-referenceData {inMemory external}     # Specifies the data from where the
                                       # post-ECO netlist is to be compared.
                                       # inMemory: Compares the post-ECO
                                       # netlist to the netlist in memory.
                                       # external: Compares the post-ECO
                                       # netlist to an external netlist.
                                       # default: inMemory (enum, optional)